The paper deals with auction mechanisms and resource allocation, which are classic topics in game theory (cs.GT) and social networks (cs.SOC). The use of social graphs and information diffusion also suggests a connection to network science (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the optimization of auction design involves mathematical modeling and information theory (cs.IT).
